# Hello world example for packing a binary Package

- https://ubuntuforums.org/showthread.php?t=910717

```sh
mkdir -p helloworld_1.0-1/usr/local/bin
cp hello.binary helloworld_1.0-1/usr/local/bin

mkdir helloworld_1.0-1/DEBIAN
edit helloworld_1.0-1/DEBIAN/control
```

Example `control` file:

```
Package: helloworld
Version: 1.0-1
Section: base
Priority: optional
Architecture: i386
Depends: libsomethingorrather (>= 1.2.13), anotherDependency (>= 1.2.6)
Maintainer: Your Name <you@email.com>
Description: Hello World
 When you need some sunshine, just run this
 small program!

 (the space before each line in the description is important)
```

```sh
dpkg-deb --build helloworld_1.0-1
```
done!

# Unpack and repack

- https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/138188/easily-unpack-deb-edit-postinst-and-repack-deb

1. `mkdir tmp`
2. `dpkg-deb -R orig.deb tmp`
3. edit tmp/DEBIAN/control
4. `dpkg-deb -b tmp fixed.deb`

# Extract contents of a .deb file

```sh
ar vx foo.deb    # -> data.tar.gz
tar xf data.tar.gz
```

# Tools

- git-buildpackage
- apt-src
- debian-builder
